WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:52.340
Ordeal

3
00:01:52.770 --> 00:01:55.140
We were tricked!

4
00:01:55.710 --> 00:01:59.810
That old lady said it, though.
"You can pass."

5
00:02:00.110 --> 00:02:02.480
And when we do,
they say it's illegal entry?!

6
00:02:02.480 --> 00:02:05.940
That's fraud! I'll sue for this!

7
00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:08.150
Right...

8
00:02:08.150 --> 00:02:11.230
Then again, even if they had said
"Don't pass through,"

9
00:02:11.230 --> 00:02:14.490
we would've entered by force anyway.

10
00:02:14.490 --> 00:02:15.450
Zip it, you!

11
00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:18.590
In any case, you are in big trouble.

12
00:02:18.590 --> 00:02:21.120
Since you've become
second-degree criminals,

13
00:02:21.120 --> 00:02:22.410
we can't...

14
00:02:22.410 --> 00:02:23.660
help you.

15
00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:26.380
Why are you talking to us
from way over there?!

16
00:02:26.380 --> 00:02:28.820
Well, what's the big deal?

17
00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:31.930
We're used to being chased.

18
00:02:33.290 --> 00:02:37.100
More importantly,
why'd you come back?

19
00:02:37.100 --> 00:02:38.010
Huh?!

20
00:02:38.010 --> 00:02:42.100
We were just about to go to that
forbidden place for a big adventu–

21
00:02:42.080 --> 00:02:46.020
Uh... I-I mean, to look for you!

22
00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:49.730
You're really easy to figure out.

23
00:02:50.730 --> 00:02:53.190
Were you about to say
"big adventure"?!

24
00:02:53.190 --> 00:02:55.410
Didn't I tell you already?!

25
00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:59.370
You're only saying that
because you haven't seen

26
00:02:59.370 --> 00:03:02.170
how terrifying the people
on that island are!

27
00:03:02.170 --> 00:03:04.290
We don't know much
about this God guy,

28
00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:07.340
but his supernatural powers
are the real thing!

29
00:03:07.340 --> 00:03:09.460
I will never go back...

30
00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:11.490
to that island!

31
00:03:13.580 --> 00:03:16.970
Then, you can just
wait here while we go.

32
00:03:16.970 --> 00:03:19.130
No way! I'll get arrested!

33
00:03:19.130 --> 00:03:20.800
We have to leave this place!

34
00:03:20.800 --> 00:03:22.590
Leave?! Are you nuts?!

35
00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:25.400
Which is more important to you,
adventure or life?!

36
00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:27.730
Life! Then money!

37
00:03:28.140 --> 00:03:30.640
Oh?! And next would be me?!

38
00:03:30.640 --> 00:03:31.940
Shut it!

39
00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:33.440
But it's true.

40
00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:37.050
Y'know, we were trying so desperately
to reach the sky island that

41
00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:39.980
how we'd get home never
even crossed our minds.

42
00:03:41.190 --> 00:03:44.870
Say, is there a way for us
to get back safely?

43
00:03:44.870 --> 00:03:47.210
Can we return to the Blue Sea?

44
00:03:48.130 --> 00:03:53.130
I can't say that it's safe,
but there is a way...

45
00:03:53.130 --> 00:03:55.670
at the farthest edge
of the clouds, Cloud End.

46
00:03:57.210 --> 00:04:00.510
Cloud End? How do we get there?

47
00:04:00.510 --> 00:04:02.930
Cloud End is far to the east.

48
00:04:02.930 --> 00:04:07.440
To get there, you need to go down
to the White Sea first.

49
00:04:07.810 --> 00:04:11.310
Great! Then, we can get back
to our sea from there, right?

50
00:04:11.310 --> 00:04:13.440
No way! I'm not going back!

51
00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:17.120
Hey, would you rather get
the death sentence here?

52
00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:21.320
In any case, staying here will cause
trouble for Conis and her dad.

53
00:04:21.670 --> 00:04:23.740
Oh, it's no trouble...

54
00:04:23.740 --> 00:04:28.230
Well, even if we run away,
they'll probably find us.

55
00:04:28.230 --> 00:04:31.120
That means it'll be the same
wherever we go in Skypiea.

56
00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:34.460
Since they know our location,
we'd better leave right away!

57
00:04:34.460 --> 00:04:36.210
Now, everyone! Let's set sail!

58
00:04:37.950 --> 00:04:41.430
Conis! Mister! Thanks for everything!

59
00:04:43.220 --> 00:04:44.500
Oh, yeah!

60
00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:45.370
Let's go, Luffy!

61
00:04:45.370 --> 00:04:47.100
Hey, old guy!

62
00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:48.890
What is it?

63
00:04:48.890 --> 00:04:52.910
Can I take all the leftover food
from earlier with me?

64
00:04:52.910 --> 00:04:54.490
Yes, of course.

65
00:04:54.490 --> 00:04:56.940
Alright! Sanji,
prepare some lunch boxes!

66
00:04:57.330 --> 00:04:59.120
No food gets by you.

67
00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:02.900
In that case, can I
ask you a favor as well?

68
00:05:02.910 --> 00:05:05.180
You're an engineer, right, old guy?

69
00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:09.180
Would you give me some
spare parts for the ship repairs?

70
00:05:09.180 --> 00:05:12.830
Sure, I don't see why not.
Then, let's go to the house again.

71
00:05:12.830 --> 00:05:15.750
Hold on! Where are you guys going?!

72
00:05:15.750 --> 00:05:17.880
I'm gonna get some food from them!

73
00:05:17.880 --> 00:05:22.810
Men! Go ahead and prepare
the ship for adventure!

74
00:05:24.390 --> 00:05:27.350
He's definitely
planning on going there.

75
00:05:27.800 --> 00:05:29.360
They really were scary!

76
00:05:29.360 --> 00:05:31.940
Who cares?!
Makes no difference to me.

77
00:05:31.940 --> 00:05:34.170
It's not my choice, anyway.

78
00:05:34.860 --> 00:05:38.640
Chopper, you're on
my side, aren't you?!

79
00:05:38.640 --> 00:05:39.900
– What?!
– Don't force him!

80
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:44.620
Heavy Point!

81
00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:52.870
I was about to drop a rope ladder.

82
00:05:52.220 --> 00:05:52.870
Oops.

83
00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:57.210
You realize that there's
no persuading Luffy, don't you?

84
00:05:57.210 --> 00:06:00.040
Even if we all protest, he won't listen.

85
00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:02.220
Fine! I won't go, then.

86
00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:04.930
Hm? So be it, then.

87
00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:07.640
"So be it"?!

88
00:06:07.640 --> 00:06:10.560
Hey, I'll be killed by those jerks!

89
00:06:11.940 --> 00:06:14.270
Ah? Then so be it.

90
00:06:17.050 --> 00:06:18.560
Why you...!

91
00:06:19.150 --> 00:06:20.110
Robin...

92
00:06:20.110 --> 00:06:22.810
why don't you and I
take down Luffy?

93
00:06:22.810 --> 00:06:23.780
That's absurd.

94
00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:28.680
I guess we've got a better chance
at taking on those jerks, huh?

95
00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:33.580
Those White Berets must be
regrouping to come after us now.

96
00:06:36.830 --> 00:06:39.300
Come after you? How foolish!

97
00:06:39.300 --> 00:06:42.370
God and his priests are
as immovable as mountains.

98
00:06:42.370 --> 00:06:45.680
They lie in wait on sacred ground
while the judged come their way.

99
00:06:45.680 --> 00:06:48.480
Once you weigh anchor,
your ordeal will start.

100
00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:50.100
You'll be led to...

101
00:06:52.490 --> 00:06:54.230
the forbidden sacred ground...

102
00:06:56.480 --> 00:06:58.210
Upper Yard!

103
00:07:01.270 --> 00:07:02.600
This is tasty!

104
00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:05.330
Hey, don't eat our lunch!

105
00:07:07.210 --> 00:07:10.060
There's a lot, so don't hold back.

106
00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:13.250
You're the one who should hold back.

107
00:07:13.250 --> 00:07:16.080
Conis, gimme some tea!

108
00:07:14.370 --> 00:07:16.080
Do it yourself!

109
00:07:16.080 --> 00:07:18.280
Oh? Conis isn't here.

110
00:07:18.280 --> 00:07:21.250
Looks like she went to bid
a fond farewell to the others.

111
00:07:21.660 --> 00:07:23.570
Here is the tea.

112
00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:30.120
So, you're the crew's shipwright?

113
00:07:30.120 --> 00:07:33.720
What? No, I'm not.
I'm a marksman.

114
00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:36.170
Oh, how fascinating!

115
00:07:36.170 --> 00:07:40.060
Right? Our ship still
doesn't have a shipwright.

116
00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:47.310
Since I'm an almighty jack of all trades,
everyone depends on me!

117
00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:50.800
It's a lot of work.

118
00:07:50.800 --> 00:07:54.580
That ship just wouldn't
function without me.

119
00:07:54.580 --> 00:07:59.570
I'm not just the marksman,
it's like I'm also co-captain.

120
00:08:00.080 --> 00:08:04.800
So everyone calls me:
Captain Usopp!

121
00:08:04.800 --> 00:08:08.260
Oh, dear! This color arrangement
is clearly done by a professional!

122
00:08:08.260 --> 00:08:11.500
Of course! Food arrangement is art.

123
00:08:12.850 --> 00:08:14.380
No, this is in the wrong place.

124
00:08:14.380 --> 00:08:19.690
I put the red one there, and put
the emerald green broad beans here.

125
00:08:21.160 --> 00:08:22.650
Now they look even tastier!

126
00:08:23.690 --> 00:08:26.460
One for my sweet Nami
and one for my lovely Robin.

127
00:08:26.460 --> 00:08:28.450
Wow, who could eat
such works of art!

128
00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:31.580
No, thank you. I'm sorry.

129
00:08:29.120 --> 00:08:31.580
I've never seen such
a pretty lunch before.

130
00:08:31.580 --> 00:08:32.370
Really?

131
00:08:32.780 --> 00:08:34.740
This is for you, Conis.

132
00:08:35.060 --> 00:08:37.460
Oh?! You made one for me, too?!

133
00:08:37.460 --> 00:08:41.150
Of course! The title of this lunch is...

134
00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:44.480
"Love is a dilemma.
Lunch for the fallen angel."

135
00:08:44.480 --> 00:08:45.210
Oh...

136
00:08:45.210 --> 00:08:47.600
Well, once it's in your stomach,

137
00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:48.770
it's all the same.

138
00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:53.470
Don't say stuff that
tears down my hard work!

139
00:08:53.470 --> 00:08:55.970
Listen up! With food,
presentation comes first!

140
00:08:55.970 --> 00:08:57.220
Really?

141
00:08:57.220 --> 00:08:58.640
See? No difference.

142
00:08:58.640 --> 00:09:00.660
Don't chow them down
without even looking!

143
00:09:01.660 --> 00:09:02.720
Why not?

144
00:09:03.950 --> 00:09:05.690
It all tastes the same, too.

145
00:09:05.690 --> 00:09:07.780
Like I said, eat them
with your eyes first!

146
00:09:10.110 --> 00:09:14.030
That's dumb.
Eyes can't eat food!

147
00:09:11.290 --> 00:09:13.050
Hmm?

148
00:09:14.030 --> 00:09:17.180
Hey! Something's wrong with the ship!

149
00:09:17.180 --> 00:09:18.620
What?!

150
00:09:18.620 --> 00:09:20.570
What's going on, Usopp?!

151
00:09:20.570 --> 00:09:22.880
Look at that! The ship's rocking!

152
00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:26.630
A party? No fair,
having a party without us!

153
00:09:26.630 --> 00:09:28.510
Ah! Nami!

154
00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:31.830
Why...

155
00:09:31.830 --> 00:09:35.310
Why is she wearing a t-shirt?!

156
00:09:35.310 --> 00:09:38.060
Just where the heck is your mind at?!

157
00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:40.890
Ahh! The ship started moving!

158
00:09:40.890 --> 00:09:43.530
What?! Why?!

159
00:09:43.530 --> 00:09:46.070
What're they doing?
Where're they going?

160
00:09:46.990 --> 00:09:51.390
Whoa! It's moving backward!
That's incredible!

161
00:09:51.390 --> 00:09:53.950
That's not it! It's not moving on its own!

162
00:09:53.950 --> 00:09:54.860
Huh?

163
00:09:56.490 --> 00:09:58.240
Look underneath the ship!

164
00:10:02.030 --> 00:10:05.520
Hold on! What is this?!
What's going on?!

165
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:08.920
That's...

166
00:10:11.980 --> 00:10:15.720
the famous White-White Sea
superexpress lobster!

167
00:10:17.820 --> 00:10:20.270
It's trying to take us somewhere!

168
00:10:20.270 --> 00:10:24.230
Hey! Everyone off the ship!
There's still time!

169
00:10:24.230 --> 00:10:27.820
What about the ship?!
If our ship is taken...

170
00:10:28.190 --> 00:10:30.610
Don't worry. I'll stay.

171
00:10:30.610 --> 00:10:34.450
C'mon! What can
you do by yourself?!

172
00:10:34.450 --> 00:10:35.920
I'll figure it out!

173
00:10:52.010 --> 00:10:53.340
Alright, this'll work!

174
00:10:54.680 --> 00:10:56.430
Unfortunately, that'd be useless.

175
00:10:58.040 --> 00:10:59.420
Come on board!

176
00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:02.390
What'd you say?!

177
00:11:02.700 --> 00:11:06.600
Even if that works, we'll just play
right into their next move. Look.

178
00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:07.810
What?!

179
00:11:13.320 --> 00:11:16.650
Large sky fish are following us
with their mouths open.

180
00:11:18.110 --> 00:11:20.530
We can't jump off
the ship to escape, now.

181
00:11:21.130 --> 00:11:25.490
Even if we defeat them,
others would likely take their place.

182
00:11:26.320 --> 00:11:29.920
There's nothing we can do.
It's probably already started.

183
00:11:29.920 --> 00:11:31.910
Divine Reckoning, huh?

184
00:11:31.910 --> 00:11:36.170
Instead of sending people after us,
he's bringing us to them.

185
00:11:36.170 --> 00:11:38.010
He's got some nerve.

186
00:11:39.640 --> 00:11:43.250
Then... I'm going back to that island?

187
00:11:44.990 --> 00:11:50.900
Luffy! Usopp! Sanji!

188
00:12:09.580 --> 00:12:12.180
Why...? Why a t-shirt...?

189
00:12:12.180 --> 00:12:13.800
You're still stuck on that?!

190
00:12:13.800 --> 00:12:17.550
Hey, Luffy! This is terrible!
What do we do?! What do we do?!

191
00:12:19.370 --> 00:12:21.680
Where'd they go?

192
00:12:21.680 --> 00:12:24.220
Of course, they... Huh?!

193
00:12:24.590 --> 00:12:25.690
So where?

194
00:12:28.060 --> 00:12:28.660
Where...

195
00:12:28.660 --> 00:12:29.200
...did they...

196
00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:29.920
...go?

197
00:12:32.200 --> 00:12:34.730
The superexpress lobster
is a messenger of God.

198
00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:38.150
What it transports is always an offering to God.

199
00:12:39.140 --> 00:12:43.040
So, it's headed to
northeast Upper Yard...

200
00:12:43.040 --> 00:12:45.360
to the sacrificial altar.

201
00:12:46.080 --> 00:12:49.520
Sacrificial altar?!
Nami, Robin, and the rest...

202
00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:50.530
The rest?!

203
00:12:50.530 --> 00:12:52.250
...will be sacrificed?!

204
00:12:52.250 --> 00:12:54.950
For that damn god?!

205
00:12:54.950 --> 00:12:57.170
That son of a bitch!

206
00:12:57.170 --> 00:12:59.720
Don't mess with us, you bastard!

207
00:13:00.230 --> 00:13:01.480
Hold on a second, please!

208
00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:04.680
But, I'm sorry! That's not the case!

209
00:13:04.680 --> 00:13:05.870
What?!

210
00:13:05.870 --> 00:13:09.340
While it can all be
considered a sacrifice,

211
00:13:09.340 --> 00:13:13.480
with Divine Reckoning, criminals
receive one of two punishments.

212
00:13:13.930 --> 00:13:16.190
Either a sacrifice or an ordeal.

213
00:13:16.190 --> 00:13:22.170
They're currently hostages
in God's hands, so to speak.

214
00:13:23.160 --> 00:13:24.870
Hostages?!

215
00:13:24.870 --> 00:13:28.450
So, the ones who are
actually being judged...

216
00:13:29.210 --> 00:13:32.330
are the three of you.

217
00:13:32.810 --> 00:13:35.050
Huh? What do you mean?

218
00:13:35.050 --> 00:13:36.300
If only I had a map...

219
00:13:36.300 --> 00:13:40.050
Oh, I actually have a map
of Skypiea with me.

220
00:13:40.920 --> 00:13:43.540
It's fairly outdated, isn't it?

221
00:13:43.540 --> 00:13:46.320
But the shape
of the island seems correct.

222
00:13:47.560 --> 00:13:49.810
This is where you are right now.

223
00:13:49.810 --> 00:13:54.990
The sacrificial altar is
up and to the left, northeast.

224
00:13:54.990 --> 00:13:58.440
To get there,
only one route is available.

225
00:14:01.420 --> 00:14:08.160
Using a dial boat, take
the milky road from this island,

226
00:14:08.160 --> 00:14:12.960
and cross over to the forest
where the priests await you.

227
00:14:18.670 --> 00:14:20.380
Well, old guy,

228
00:14:20.380 --> 00:14:23.380
instead of winding our way
through the island,

229
00:14:23.380 --> 00:14:27.300
all we have to do is go
around it by boat, right?

230
00:14:28.480 --> 00:14:32.980
That lobster went to Upper Yard
that way, too, didn't it?

231
00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:34.140
Well...

232
00:14:34.140 --> 00:14:40.320
even if you make landfall near
the altar, it's inaccessible by foot.

233
00:14:40.680 --> 00:14:44.240
This map is far different
from today's Upper Yard,

234
00:14:44.240 --> 00:14:47.230
because milky roads now
stretch all around the island.

235
00:14:48.400 --> 00:14:50.190
Those are the cloud canals, right?

236
00:14:50.190 --> 00:14:54.210
Yes. I hear that there are
several hundred milky roads,

237
00:14:54.210 --> 00:14:56.270
large and small in size, over there.

238
00:14:56.270 --> 00:14:57.960
Hmm... I see...

239
00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:01.680
That is why entering
the island by boat

240
00:15:01.680 --> 00:15:05.970
and taking the milky roads
within is the only way.

241
00:15:05.970 --> 00:15:08.290
I see.

242
00:15:08.290 --> 00:15:12.890
So no matter where we try to dock,
the canals will block our way.

243
00:15:12.890 --> 00:15:14.260
That's right.

244
00:15:14.260 --> 00:15:17.480
By the way, there are also
man-eating fish in the canals.

245
00:15:17.480 --> 00:15:18.980
Man-eating fish?!

246
00:15:18.980 --> 00:15:21.490
They've really covered all their bases.

247
00:15:23.310 --> 00:15:25.920
So, in order to get
our friends and ship back,

248
00:15:26.900 --> 00:15:30.010
we just have to come in
from the front.

249
00:15:31.320 --> 00:15:35.540
So that's our ordeal...
and Divine Reckoning?!

250
00:15:35.540 --> 00:15:42.330
Yes. Four unimaginably strong 
priests await you in Upper Yard.

251
00:15:44.680 --> 00:15:47.470
That's it? Sounds easy to me.

252
00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:52.540
In other words, all we have to do
is beat up those priests, right?

253
00:15:52.540 --> 00:15:54.240
You're so simple-minded.

254
00:15:58.230 --> 00:16:00.330
This is getting fun!

255
00:16:02.390 --> 00:16:02.440
Lovely Street
Angel Beach

